			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I know this sounds dumb, but one idea I was thinking about was something akin to the ranger's jolt line of spells, for the purpose of reducing agro.
<br />

<br />
Perhaps as a pet proc, that reduces agro not just on pet, but on both pet and master around the neg 500 points that rogue evade does?  Every other non-tank melee, has a way of mitigating agro but us.  Warriors have discs, paladins have divine aura, rangers have jolt, bards have a number of songs, rogues have evade/escape, monks just keel over, SK's keel over and smell funny or harmshield, but BL's, the main way of mitigating agro is to hope pet can taunt enough so you can back off.
<br />

<br />
Maybe a dumb idea, but just seeing what other people think.
<br />

<br />
EDITED:  Killed some typos.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
