			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">It is my personal opinion that BL do not need a spell or other ability of this nature.
<br />

<br />
Agro management is one of the few aspects in the game that can make combat tactical.  Asking for a power that voids the need for tactical thinking does not appeal to me.
<br />

<br />
Lets quickly look at the other classes.
<br />

<br />
Warriors get /discs.  Although warriors actually want to get agro, and the /disc I think you are refering to is defensive (this is the one that would let them survive having agro) actually slightly reduces their ability to do damage, and hence hold agro.  In fact - in many ways you cant compare with warriors, who actually want ways of increasing agro - not decreasing it - BUT - we have /disc protective to help us survive agro, and /disc beast if for some reason you needed it to get agro.
<br />

<br />
Monks get FD.  Its pretty ultimate at getting rid of agro.  And they can do absolutely zero damage while they have feigned and are waiting for the mob to forget them, or for another character to out agro them.  (At lower levels FD clears agro fast, higher level mobs, such as anything in PoP, tend to have longer memories)
<br />

<br />
Rogues get evade.  It doesnt always work, but it is pretty good.  But unlike all other melees, rogues are absolutely dependent on not having agro, or they loose a huge chunk of their DPS.  And there are times that even a successful evade wont be enough to loose agro, especially when there are a bunch of evenly agroing melees in the group.  Their option is limited then to stopping attack and loosing DPS while other melees get more hate up.
<br />

<br />
SKs get FD and harmshield.  In both cases, they can no longer deal damage while the effects of the spells work.  Although their DoTs might still be going.
<br />

<br />
Pallies get DA.  And can not do any damage while it is up.
<br />

<br />
Rangers get Jolt and Jolting blades.  Rangers originally got this line because no one could taunt off a ranger (and rangers really had to melee to do DPS, archery still sucked), but nowdays pallies can manage with their stuns.  But using jolting blades means giving up a damage proc spell, and loosing DPS.  Using Jolt is better.  But even with jolt, a ranger is in danger of stealing agro unless they town down their DPS appropriately.  And with archery, rangers dont need jolt anyway.
<br />

<br />
Wizzies get concussion, and clever use of this and nukes can keep them from getting agro.  If they pace themselves and dont try to do too much daamge.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Hmm - look at that - even with these powers, the classes still need to control their damage to match the taunt capacity of their tank.  Isnt that interesting?
<br />

<br />

<br />
Now BL.  To my mind - BL have about the best agro avoiding ability imaginable - the pet.  Not sure what level you are, but for me, I never have to hold agro more than a few seconds if I dont want it.  Between hate increasing procs and a good taunt skill, my pet rapidly overtakes me on any mob's hate list.  All I ever have to do to avoid getting pasted is use /disc protective and/or step away from the mob.
<br />

<br />
Its that easy - step away.  If pet doesnt have agro, she will in seconds.
<br />

<br />

<br />
But whats that?  If I step away - I loose my melee DPS?  Of course I do.  Its called 'agro management' or 'controling my DPS' and any competent player should learn how to do it.  There are times when you simply have to limit how much damage you do to allow for your tank.  Jolt/evade/FD included - its all managing your agro.
<br />

<br />
And even when I am out of melee range - my pet is still providing her DPS.  Monks cant FD and deliver damage like that.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Again my opinion, but BL do NOT need jolt/evade/FD to control agro.  The mechanics of pet agro are a very powerful means of saving our bacon if you just use it.
<br />

<br />

<br />
But I understand, you think we should be able to do our full DPS, with nuke sand DoTs and melee and pet, and never draw agro.  Wizzies think that too.  Warriors silently wish that too.  But it is not the case.  And I think the combat in the game, mindless as it sometimes is, is still better for the fact that you have to at least think a little bit about what you are doing.
<br />

<br />

<br />
And finally - the easiest solution - is to tank.  If you really can't (or more likely wont) manage your agro, then take the hits.
<br />

<br />

<br />
I bet shammies would like some agro reducing powers too.  After malo and slow, why, they probably already have agro.  I bet they would love to stack up 200 DPS worth of DoTs as well.  I bet clerics would love agro reduction, an early CHeal gets them no end of trouble - and with DA on they cant heal.....  I bet druids would like it too, and I am certain mages would love it, the chance to nuke like mad yet keep agro with their pet.  But instead these classes go manage their agro properly.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Anyway - I dont think BL need any sort of additional agro reducing ability at all.  I think we already have a perfectly viable and effective way of dealing with mob hate, which is balanced with all the other classes who have to take active effort to manage their hate and control their DPS.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
